and being\nthe wives of Brahm\xc4\x81, Vish\xe1\xb9\x87u, and Ru\xe1\xb8\x8dra.\n\n[181:1](tmu24.htm#fr_138) This passage clearly indicates the dreadful\nconsequences of the performance of Pr\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81y\xc4\x81ma rashly and without a guru.\n\n[181:2](tmu24.htm#fr_139) As already pointed out, the Sushumn\xc4\x81 n\xc4\x81di is between\nId\xc4\x81 and Pi\xe1\xb9\x85gal\xc4\x81. If Pr\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87a which alternates ordinarily between Id\xc4\x81 and Pi\xe1\xb9\x85gal\xc4\x81\nis restrained by long p. 182 kumbhaka, then it along with the soul, its\nattendant will enter the Sushumn\xc4\x81 (central n\xc4\x81di) at one of the three places\nwhere it yields space for entrance through such restraint of breath and in the\nnavel, from the Sarasva\xe1\xb9\xad\xc4\xab n\xc4\x81di on the west. After such entry it is that the\nyogin becomes dead to the world, being in the state called trance.\n\n[182:1](tmu24.htm#fr_140) Through such and other methods of Pr\xc4\x81\xe1\xb9\x87\xc4\x81y\xc4\x81ma\nprescribed in this passage and the subsequent ones, chronic diseases that defy\nEuropean doctors will be rooted out.\n\n[182:2](tmu24.htm#fr_141) He becomes an \xc5\xaar\xe1\xb8\x8dhva-r\xc4\x93\xe1\xb9\xadas--his vital energy goes\nup.\n\n[183:1](tmu24.htm#fr_142) There are six centres of energy in the body\n(m\xc5\xabl\xc4\x81\xe1\xb8\x8dh\xc4\x81ra, sacral plexus, etc.), which are presided over by six sak\xe1\xb9\xadis\n(goddesses of energy).\n\n[184:1](tmu24.htm#fr_143) This twelfth centre is identified by some with the\npituitary body in the head, there being six centres in the brain besides the\nsix below the brain.\n\n[186:1](tmu24.htm#fr_144) Lit., binding the air up the throat.\n\n[187:1](tmu24.htm#fr_153) These correspond severally to the several directions\nand the \xe1\xb8\x8deva\xe1\xb9\xad\xc4\x81s presiding over them, corresponding respectively to east,\nsouth-east, south, southwest, west, north-west, north, and north-east.\n\n[187:2](tmu24.htm#fr_154) The fourteen worlds, lokas and \xe1\xb9\xadalas are referred\nto; the order in \xe1\xb9\xadalas seems to be wrong, \xe1\xb9\xacala\xe1\xb9\xadala should be in the middle.\n\n[189:1](tmu24.htm#fr_155) Some texts leave the words "and yoga".\n\n[190:1](tmu24.htm#fr_157) These relate to the G\xc4\x81ya\xe1\xb9\xadr\xc4\xab man\xe1\xb9\xadras depending upon\nsound.\n\n[190:2](tmu24.htm#fr_158) According to Bh\xc4\x81gava\xe1\xb9\xada, he is one of the minor\nincarnations of Vish\xe1\xb9\x87u.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 23. Yoga\xe1\xb9\xada\xe1\xb9\xad\xe1\xb9\xadva-Upanisha\xe1\xb8\x8d of K\xe1\xb9\x9bsh\xe1\xb9\x87a-Yajurve\xe1\xb8\x8da](tmu25.htm)\n\n'